<br>
Couple mythos tha Ah have heard:<br>
<br>
1, Werewolves have no control over their ability to change a person (or any lycanthrope in fact) and animals are not effected by it - it is a lycanthrope - human disease only.<br>
<br>
The only way this occues is if a human survives an attack. (Which usually does not occur - hence the lack of us seeing lycanthropes running around the area) . . . <br>
<br>
2, Lycanthrope starts as an uncontrolled behavior but in the case of its being trained ie that is of two different mythos - one is Eurupean / Ahh dammit ferget the other location in nature. And the other mythos is far Germanic and that lycanthropy is not trainable and eventually will consume the person till they become the animal in its entirety - wolf, tiger, bear etc.<br>
<br>
============================================<br>
<br>
Vampires<br>
<br>
Long mythos - but two that I know of<br>
<br>
1, The vampire is entirely in control if its ability to change the person or beast it bites period.<br>
<br>
a, It can not do anything to the victim by its bite other than kill it entirely ( tear the crap outa it like an animal -- ouchie)<br>
<br>
b, It can turn it into a walking corpse -desiring only to drink blood (prolly cause it has none left in itself heh) and under the control of the master - and stinking of corpse<br>
<br>
c, Or turned into a vampire in two ways: loving the master or hating the master -- Master better be damn careful of the &quot;victims&quot; desires before performing this ritual!!!<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
2, The Oriental Vampire is a Wild Spirit - with NO control over itself or what it does - Don't know much about it but that the Chinese fear this creature terribly.<br>
<br>
It kills and kills and kills. I believe it will turn whole villages into walking dead seeking victims but may not recreate itself.<br>
<br>
I have no idea how a Vampire of Chinese origin is created - but something tickles my memory that it is created by some foul deed of greed or murder ie A person does something in their life that DEMANDS soul payment and when they die they are reincarnated as a vampire.<br>
<br>
That is all I know. Hope it helps<br>
